  <h1>Lone Pine</h1><div>
<br>Lone Pine is a small town just east of the Sierra Navada mountains, about an hour or so outside of Death Valley.&nbsp; It's also near the Alabama Hills, which are famous as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lone_Pine,_California#Film_history_at_Lone_Pine">setting for movies</a> such as Tremors (with the esteemed Kevin Bacon), and many other lesser-known films.&nbsp; On the way to Lone Pine are two other sites:&nbsp; <a href="https://www.nps.gov/manz/index.htm">Manzanar</a>, one of the WWII Japanese detainment camps; and the <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/inyo/specialplaces/?cid=stelprdb5129900">Ancient Bristlecone Pine Forest</a>, home to the oldest single living thing we've been able to measure.&nbsp; Unfortunately Carrie and I did not get to stop at either of these places -- they'll have to be for the next grand roadtrip.<br><br>In brighter news, however, our <a href="https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/12407656">awesome airbnb</a> was filled with cat things.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lODMzZjM4ZS04ZDZlLTRjYzEtOTJlZi1hZTc3Nzg1ZTVlMGI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--80eb2ba22596e9dcf6b45bd10233273f4fc1df15" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsT0RNelpqTTRaUzA0WkRabExUUmpZekV0T1RKbFppMWhaVGMzTnpnMVpUVmxNR0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--893bdf5765177c611f3a49968a4d608dcfaf8125/IMG_2996.jpg" filename="IMG_2996.jpg" filesize="208340" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Lone Pine sits right between the Sierra Nevada and Inyo Mountains"><figure class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--jpg">
